at the MW EPs might\nexperience a mass loss up to $\\sim 15$ times the Mars atmosphere over a period\nof $50$ Myr as the result of exposure to the cumulative extreme-UV flux\n$F_{\\textrm{XUV}}$ from the AGNs up to $z = 0.5$. In both cases we found that\nan incorrect choice of $\\epsilon$ can lead to significant mass loss\noverestimates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Feb 2019 10:36:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-17"}
