rators only corroborate existing calibration\nmeasurements. Nonetheless, astrophysical calibration may become an important\ncorroboration of existing calibration methods, providing a completely\nindependent constraint of potential systematics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Feb 2019 14:44:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-04"}
