{"id":"1902.08107","submitter":"Pratik Suchde","authors":"Pratik Suchde, Joerg Kuhnert","title":"A Fully Lagrangian Meshfree Framework for PDEs on Evolving Surfaces","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Journal of Computational Physics, 395: 38-59. 2019","doi":"10.1016/j.jcp.2019.06.031","report-no":null,"categories":"math.NA cs.NA physics.comp-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We propose a novel framework to solve PDEs on moving manifolds, where the\nevolving surface is represented by a moving point cloud. This has the advantage\nof avoiding the need to discretize the bulk volume around the surface, while\nalso avoiding the need to have a global mesh. Distortions in the point cloud as\na result of the movement are fixed by local adaptation. We first establish a\ncomprehensive Lagrangian framework for arbitrary movement of curves and\nsurfaces given by point clouds. Collision detection algorithms between point\ncloud surfaces are introduced, which also allow the handling of evolving\nmanifolds with topological changes. We then couple this Lagrangian framework\nwith a meshfree Generalized Finite Difference Method (GFDM) to approximate\nsurface differential operators, which together give a method to solve PDEs on\nevolving manifolds. The applicability of this method is illustrated with a\nrange of numerical examples, which include advection-diffusion equations with\nlarge deformations of the surface, curvature dependent geometric motion, and\nwave equations on evolving surfaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Feb 2019 15:49:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Jun 2019 09:28:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-20"}
